.TH MAKE_GENBANK_PROJ_FILE 1 2026-4月 "internal" "Initialize a Single GenBank Project and Export Sequence Files"
.SH NAME
make_genbank_proj_file \- make_genbank_proj_file(src, release.dir,
    <i>workdir</i> = <span style='color: brown;'><strong>''</strong></span>,
    <i>batch.process</i> = <span style='color: blue !important;'>FALSE</span>)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fImake_genbank_proj_file(src, release.dir,
    <i>workdir</i> = <span style='color: brown;'><strong>''</strong></span>,
    <i>batch.process</i> = <span style='color: blue !important;'>FALSE</span>)\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Core processing function that ingests a GenBank file, wraps it into a
standardized \code{project} object via \code{CellRender}, saves the
project state to disk, and extracts essential FASTA files required for
downstream bioinformatics analyses (motif scanning and homology searches).
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fBsrc\fB \fR\- . Character. The file path to a single GenBank source file.
.PP
.PP
\fBrelease.dir\fB \fR\- . 
.PP
.PP
\fBworkdir\fB \fR\- ''. Character. The working directory where extracted FASTA
files will be written.
.PP
.PP
\fBbatch.process\fB \fR\- FALSE. 
.PP
.SH VALUE
.PP
Returns \code{invisible(NULL)}. Upon execution, it generates the
following local files:
\itemize{
\item \strong{Project File:} \code{builder.gcproj} containing the
parsed GenBank project data.
\item \strong{upstream_locis.fasta:} TSS (Transcription Start Site)
upstream sequences, prepared for downstream motif site scanning.
\item \strong{proteins.fasta:} Genomic protein sequences, prepared
for enzyme and Transcription Factor (TF) annotation via DIAMOND BLASTp.
}
.PP
.SH FILES
.PP
SMRUCC/R#.declare_function.make_genbank_proj_file at make_genbank_proj.R:line 115
.PP
